org.pikater.shared.database.jpa

Class JPADataSetLO

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pikater.shared.database.jpa.JPAAbstractEntity
      • org.pikater.shared.database.jpa.JPADataSetLO

  • @Entity
public class JPADataSetLO
extends JPAAbstractEntity
    Class JPADataSetLO represents record about the datasets available in the database. These datasets are stored in large object files and this class just contains the ID of that particular large object.

    Datasets have certain metadata, that are stored using several additional classes.

    See Also:
    JPAAttributeMetaData, JPAGlobalMetaData

      • JPADataSetLO

        public JPADataSetLO(JPAUser owner)
        Cretes a new JPA Entity insance of dataset. To store the entity please use DataSetDAO.storeNewDataSet(File dataset,JPADataSetLO initialData) function which will automatically compute the Hash for the given DataSet and if necessary stores the File to Database.
        Parameters:
        owner - JPAUser owner of the DataSet

      • JPADataSetLO

        public JPADataSetLO(JPAUser owner,
            java.lang.String description)
        Cretes a new JPA Entity insance of dataset. To store the entity please use DataSetDAO.storeNewDataSet(File dataset,JPADataSetLO initialData) function which will automatically compute the Hash for the given DataSet and if necessary stores the File to Database
        Parameters:
        owner - JPAUser owner of the DataSet
        description - Some Description of the Dataset
